##"If the new coronavirus continues to spread, corporate schools in the United States will be forced to close. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Nan Boyi, _ the_paper _ reporter

On February 21st US health officials said the US was preparing for the possibility of community-based transmission of the new coronavirus, which would force the closure of businesses and schools.

There has been no community-based transmission of the new coronavirus in the United States, but health authorities are preparing for the risk, Nancy Messonnier, an official with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, said Tuesday in a telephone news conference.

In the coming weeks, health authorities will have to take steps similar to those taken in Asia to prepare for school and business closures if the new coronavirus starts spreading in communities in the United States, Meisner said.

"We haven't seen the new coronavirus enter the community-based phase of transmission in the United States, but it's very likely to happen, " Dr. Meisner said, "Our goal now remains to slow the spread of the new coronavirus in the United States. This will buy us more time to prepare for the treatment of more cases and to deal with the continued spread of the virus. "

The CDC says there are currently 13 confirmed cases of the disease in the United States. There were also 21 confirmed cases among US citizens evacuated from the Chinese cruises Wuhan and the Diamond Princess.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is still doing most of the testing for the new coronavirus in the country and is working to address the issue of testing kits being sent to states, Maisonier said.

The American Association of Public Health Laboratories (APHL) said Tuesday that only three states in the United States currently have the capacity to conduct local tests for the new coronavirus.

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
